title: Classic Spaghetti Aglio e Olio
instructions: Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add the spaghetti and cook according to package directions until al dente.
While the pasta cooks, thinly slice the garlic cloves.

In a large skillet, heat the olive oil over low heat. Add the sliced garlic and red pepper flakes. Cook slowly for 5-7 minutes until the garlic is fragrant and lightly golden. Do not let the garlic burn.
Before draining the pasta, reserve about 1 cup of the starchy cooking water.
Drain the spaghetti and immediately transfer it to the skillet with the garlic oil.
Toss the pasta vigorously, adding a few tablespoons of the reserved pasta water at a time, until a light, emulsified sauce coats the spaghetti.
Stir in the chopped fresh parsley. Taste and adjust seasoning with salt if necessary.
